{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I love a challenge, and saving the Earth is probably a good one."},{"time":4000,"text":"We all know the Earth is in trouble."},{"time":6000,"text":"We have now entered in the 6X,"},{"time":8000,"text":"the sixth major extinction on this planet."},{"time":11000,"text":"I often wondered, if there was a United Organization of Organisms --"},{"time":14000,"text":"otherwise known as \"Uh-Oh\" --"},{"time":16000,"text":"(Laughter) -- and every organism had a right to vote,"},{"time":19000,"text":"would we be voted on the planet, or off the planet?"},{"time":22000,"text":"I think that vote is occurring right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"I want to present to you a suite of six mycological solutions,"},{"time":28000,"text":"using fungi, and these solutions are based on mycelium."},{"time":35000,"text":"The mycelium infuses all landscapes,"},{"time":38000,"text":"it holds soils together, it's extremely tenacious."},{"time":41000,"text":"This holds up to 30,000 times its mass."},{"time":44000,"text":"They're the grand molecular disassemblers of nature -- the soil magicians."},{"time":47000,"text":"They generate the humus soils across the landmasses of Earth."},{"time":51000,"text":"We have now discovered that there is a multi-directional transfer"},{"time":56000,"text":"of nutrients between plants, mitigated by the mcyelium --"},{"time":60000,"text":"so the mycelium is the mother"},{"time":62000,"text":"that is giving nutrients from alder and birch trees"},{"time":64000,"text":"to hemlocks, cedars and Douglas firs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"Dusty and I, we like to say, on Sunday, this is where we go to church."},{"time":71000,"text":"I'm in love with the old-growth forest,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and I'm a patriotic American because we have those."},{"time":77000,"text":"Most of you are familiar with Portobello mushrooms."},{"time":80000,"text":"And frankly, I face a big obstacle."},{"time":82000,"text":"When I mention mushrooms to somebody,"},{"time":84000,"text":"they immediately think Portobellos or magic mushrooms,"},{"time":86000,"text":"their eyes glaze over, and they think I'm a little crazy."},{"time":89000,"text":"So, I hope to pierce that prejudice forever with this group."},{"time":92000,"text":"We call it mycophobia,"},{"time":94000,"text":"the irrational fear of the unknown, when it comes to fungi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"Mushrooms are very fast in their growth."},{"time":102000,"text":"Day 21, day 23, day 25."},{"time":106000,"text":"Mushrooms produce strong antibiotics."},{"time":108000,"text":"In fact, we're more closely related to fungi than we are to any other kingdom."},{"time":111000,"text":"A group of 20 eukaryotic microbiologists"},{"time":114000,"text":"published a paper two years ago erecting opisthokonta --"},{"time":117000,"text":"a super-kingdom that joins animalia and fungi together."},{"time":120000,"text":"We share in common the same pathogens."},{"time":123000,"text":"Fungi don't like to rot from bacteria,"},{"time":125000,"text":"and so our best antibiotics come from fungi."},{"time":129000,"text":"But here is a mushroom that's past its prime."},{"time":131000,"text":"After they sporulate, they do rot."},{"time":133000,"text":"But I propose to you that the sequence of microbes"},{"time":136000,"text":"that occur on rotting mushrooms"},{"time":138000,"text":"are essential for the health of the forest."},{"time":140000,"text":"They give rise to the trees,"},{"time":142000,"text":"they create the debris fields that feed the mycelium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"And so we see a mushroom here sporulating."},{"time":148000,"text":"And the spores are germinating,"},{"time":150000,"text":"and the mycelium forms and goes underground."},{"time":153000,"text":"In a single cubic inch of soil, there can be more than eight miles of these cells."},{"time":157000,"text":"My foot is covering approximately 300 miles of mycelium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160000,"text":"This is photomicrographs from Nick Read and Patrick Hickey."},{"time":165000,"text":"And notice that as the mycelium grows,"},{"time":167000,"text":"it conquers territory and then it begins the net."},{"time":173000,"text":"I've been a scanning electron microscopist for many years,"},{"time":176000,"text":"I have thousands of electron micrographs,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and when I'm staring at the mycelium,"},{"time":180000,"text":"I realize that they are microfiltration membranes."},{"time":182000,"text":"We exhale carbon dioxide, so does mycelium."},{"time":185000,"text":"It inhales oxygen, just like we do."},{"time":188000,"text":"But these are essentially externalized stomachs and lungs."},{"time":192000,"text":"And I present to you a concept that these are extended neurological membranes."},{"time":197000,"text":"And in these cavities, these micro-cavities form,"},{"time":200000,"text":"and as they fuse soils, they absorb water."},{"time":202000,"text":"These are little wells."},{"time":204000,"text":"And inside these wells, then microbial communities begin to form."},{"time":207000,"text":"And so the spongy soil not only resists erosion,"},{"time":211000,"text":"but sets up a microbial universe"},{"time":213000,"text":"that gives rise to a plurality of other organisms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218000,"text":"I first proposed, in the early 1990s,"},{"time":220000,"text":"that mycelium is Earth's natural Internet."},{"time":224000,"text":"When you look at the mycelium, they're highly branched."},{"time":229000,"text":"And if there's one branch that is broken, then very quickly,"},{"time":234000,"text":"because of the nodes of crossing --"},{"time":236000,"text":"Internet engineers maybe call them hot points --"},{"time":238000,"text":"there are alternative pathways for channeling nutrients and information."},{"time":243000,"text":"The mycelium is sentient."},{"time":245000,"text":"It knows that you are there."},{"time":247000,"text":"When you walk across landscapes,"},{"time":249000,"text":"it leaps up in the aftermath of your footsteps trying to grab debris."},{"time":256000,"text":"So, I believe the invention of the computer Internet"},{"time":260000,"text":"is an inevitable consequence"},{"time":262000,"text":"of a previously proven, biologically successful model."},{"time":265000,"text":"The Earth invented the computer Internet for its own benefit,"},{"time":269000,"text":"and we now, being the top organism on this planet,"},{"time":273000,"text":"are trying to allocate resources in order to protect the biosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"Going way out, dark matter conforms to the same mycelial archetype."},{"time":284000,"text":"I believe matter begets life;"},{"time":286000,"text":"life becomes single cells; single cells become strings;"},{"time":289000,"text":"strings become chains; chains network."},{"time":292000,"text":"And this is the paradigm that we see throughout the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298000,"text":"Most of you may not know that fungi were the first organisms to come to land."},{"time":301000,"text":"They came to land 1.3 billion years ago,"},{"time":304000,"text":"and plants followed several hundred million years later."},{"time":307000,"text":"How is that possible?"},{"time":309000,"text":"It's possible because the mycelium produces oxalic acids,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and many other acids and enzymes,"},{"time":314000,"text":"pockmarking rock and grabbing calcium and other minerals"},{"time":318000,"text":"and forming calcium oxalates."},{"time":320000,"text":"Makes the rocks crumble, and the first step in the generation of soil."},{"time":325000,"text":"Oxalic acid is two carbon dioxide molecules joined together."},{"time":329000,"text":"So, fungi and mycelium"},{"time":331000,"text":"sequester carbon dioxide in the form of calcium oxalates."},{"time":335000,"text":"And all sorts of other oxalates"},{"time":337000,"text":"are also sequestering carbon dioxide through the minerals"},{"time":340000,"text":"that are being formed and taken out of the rock matrix."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"This was first discovered in 1859."},{"time":346000,"text":"This is a photograph by Franz Hueber."},{"time":348000,"text":"This photograph's taken 1950s in Saudi Arabia."},{"time":351000,"text":"420 million years ago, this organism existed."},{"time":355000,"text":"It was called Prototaxites."},{"time":357000,"text":"Prototaxites, laying down, was about three feet tall."},{"time":361000,"text":"The tallest plants on Earth at that time were less than two feet."},{"time":366000,"text":"Dr. Boyce, at the University of Chicago,"},{"time":370000,"text":"published an article in the Journal of Geology"},{"time":373000,"text":"this past year determining that Prototaxites was a giant fungus,"},{"time":379000,"text":"a giant mushroom."},{"time":381000,"text":"Across the landscapes of Earth were dotted these giant mushrooms."},{"time":385000,"text":"All across most land masses."},{"time":388000,"text":"And these existed for tens of millions of years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"Now, we've had several extinction events, and as we march forward --"},{"time":395000,"text":"65 million years ago -- most of you know about it --"},{"time":398000,"text":"we had an asteroid impact."},{"time":400000,"text":"The Earth was struck by an asteroid,"},{"time":402000,"text":"a huge amount of debris was jettisoned into the atmosphere."},{"time":406000,"text":"Sunlight was cut off, and fungi inherited the Earth."},{"time":411000,"text":"Those organisms that paired with fungi were rewarded,"},{"time":415000,"text":"because fungi do not need light."},{"time":418000,"text":"More recently, at Einstein University,"},{"time":420000,"text":"they just determined that fungi use radiation as a source of energy,"},{"time":425000,"text":"much like plants use light."},{"time":427000,"text":"So, the prospect of fungi existing on other planets elsewhere,"},{"time":431000,"text":"I think, is a forgone conclusion,"},{"time":433000,"text":"at least in my own mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"The largest organism in the world is in Eastern Oregon."},{"time":438000,"text":"I couldn't miss it. It was 2,200 acres in size:"},{"time":441000,"text":"2,200 acres in size, 2,000 years old."},{"time":445000,"text":"The largest organism on the planet is a mycelial mat, one cell wall thick."},{"time":449000,"text":"How is it that this organism can be so large,"},{"time":454000,"text":"and yet be one cell wall thick,"},{"time":456000,"text":"whereas we have five or six skin layers that protect us?"},{"time":458000,"text":"The mycelium, in the right conditions, produces a mushroom --"},{"time":461000,"text":"it bursts through with such ferocity that it can break asphalt."},{"time":464000,"text":"We were involved with several experiments."},{"time":467000,"text":"I'm going to show you six, if I can,"},{"time":469000,"text":"solutions for helping to save the world."},{"time":471000,"text":"Battelle Laboratories and I joined up in Bellingham, Washington."},{"time":474000,"text":"There were four piles saturated with diesel and other petroleum waste:"},{"time":478000,"text":"one was a control pile; one pile was treated with enzymes;"},{"time":482000,"text":"one pile was treated with bacteria;"},{"time":486000,"text":"and our pile we inoculated with mushroom mycelium."},{"time":488000,"text":"The mycelium absorbs the oil."},{"time":491000,"text":"The mycelium is producing enzymes --"},{"time":493000,"text":"peroxidases -- that break carbon-hydrogen bonds."},{"time":496000,"text":"These are the same bonds that hold hydrocarbons together."},{"time":499000,"text":"So, the mycelium becomes saturated with the oil,"},{"time":502000,"text":"and then, when we returned six weeks later,"},{"time":505000,"text":"all the tarps were removed,"},{"time":507000,"text":"all the other piles were dead, dark and stinky."},{"time":509000,"text":"We came back to our pile, it was covered"},{"time":511000,"text":"with hundreds of pounds of oyster mushrooms,"},{"time":512000,"text":"and the color changed to a light form."},{"time":515000,"text":"The enzymes remanufactured the hydrocarbons"},{"time":518000,"text":"into carbohydrates -- fungal sugars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"Some of these mushrooms are very happy mushrooms."},{"time":522000,"text":"They're very large."},{"time":524000,"text":"They're showing how much nutrition that they could've obtained."},{"time":526000,"text":"But something else happened, which was an epiphany in my life."},{"time":530000,"text":"They sporulated, the spores attract insects,"},{"time":532000,"text":"the insects laid eggs, eggs became larvae."},{"time":536000,"text":"Birds then came, bringing in seeds,"},{"time":538000,"text":"and our pile became an oasis of life."},{"time":540000,"text":"Whereas the other three piles were dead, dark and stinky,"},{"time":544000,"text":"and the PAH's -- the aromatic hydrocarbons --"},{"time":547000,"text":"went from 10,000 parts per million to less than 200 in eight weeks."},{"time":551000,"text":"The last image we don't have."},{"time":554000,"text":"The entire pile was a green berm of life."},{"time":556000,"text":"These are gateway species,"},{"time":558000,"text":"vanguard species that open the door for other biological communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563000,"text":"So I invented burlap sacks, bunker spawn --"},{"time":567000,"text":"and putting the mycelium -- using storm blown debris,"},{"time":570000,"text":"you can take these burlap sacks and put them downstream"},{"time":573000,"text":"from a farm that's producing E. coli, or other wastes,"},{"time":576000,"text":"or a factory with chemical toxins,"},{"time":578000,"text":"and it leads to habitat restoration."},{"time":580000,"text":"So, we set up a site in Mason County, Washington,"},{"time":583000,"text":"and we've seen a dramatic decrease in the amount of coliforms."},{"time":586000,"text":"And I'll show you a graph here."},{"time":589000,"text":"This is a logarithmic scale, 10 to the eighth power."},{"time":591000,"text":"There's more than a 100 million colonies per gram,"},{"time":594000,"text":"and 10 to the third power is around 1,000."},{"time":597000,"text":"In 48 hours to 72 hours, these three mushroom species"},{"time":601000,"text":"reduced the amount of coliform bacteria 10,000 times."},{"time":605000,"text":"Think of the implications."},{"time":607000,"text":"This is a space-conservative method that uses storm debris --"},{"time":611000,"text":"and we can guarantee that we will have storms every year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613000,"text":"So, this one mushroom, in particular, has drawn our interest over time."},{"time":618000,"text":"This is my wife Dusty,"},{"time":620000,"text":"with a mushroom called Fomitopsis officinalis -- Agarikon."},{"time":622000,"text":"It's a mushroom exclusive to the old-growth forest"},{"time":625000,"text":"that Dioscorides first described in 65 A.D."},{"time":627000,"text":"as a treatment against consumption."},{"time":629000,"text":"This mushroom grows in Washington State, Oregon,"},{"time":632000,"text":"northern California, British Columbia, now thought to be extinct in Europe."},{"time":635000,"text":"May not seem that large --"},{"time":637000,"text":"let's get closer."},{"time":639000,"text":"This is extremely rare fungus."},{"time":641000,"text":"Our team -- and we have a team of experts that go out --"},{"time":644000,"text":"we went out 20 times in the old-growth forest last year."},{"time":647000,"text":"We found one sample to be able to get into culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650000,"text":"Preserving the genome of these fungi in the old-growth forest"},{"time":654000,"text":"I think is absolutely critical for human health."},{"time":657000,"text":"I've been involved with the U.S. Defense Department BioShield program."},{"time":661000,"text":"We submitted over 300 samples of mushrooms that were boiled in hot water,"},{"time":664000,"text":"and mycelium harvesting these extracellular metabolites."},{"time":667000,"text":"And a few years ago,"},{"time":670000,"text":"we received these results."},{"time":673000,"text":"We have three different strains of Agarikon mushrooms"},{"time":678000,"text":"that were highly active against poxviruses."},{"time":680000,"text":"Dr. Earl Kern, who's a smallpox expert"},{"time":683000,"text":"of the U.S. Defense Department, states that any compounds"},{"time":685000,"text":"that have a selectivity index of two or more are active."},{"time":688000,"text":"10 or greater are considered to be very active."},{"time":690000,"text":"Our mushroom strains were in the highly active range."},{"time":694000,"text":"There's a vetted press release that you can read --"},{"time":697000,"text":"it's vetted by DOD --"},{"time":699000,"text":"if you Google \"Stamets\" and \"smallpox.\""},{"time":701000,"text":"Or you can go to NPR.org and listen to a live interview."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704000,"text":"So, encouraged by this, naturally we went to flu viruses."},{"time":709000,"text":"And so, for the first time, I am showing this."},{"time":712000,"text":"We have three different strains of Agarikon mushrooms"},{"time":715000,"text":"highly active against flu viruses."},{"time":717000,"text":"Here's the selectivity index numbers --"},{"time":719000,"text":"against pox, you saw 10s and 20s -- now against flu viruses,"},{"time":722000,"text":"compared to the ribavirin controls,"},{"time":724000,"text":"we have an extraordinarily high activity."},{"time":727000,"text":"And we're using a natural extract"},{"time":729000,"text":"within the same dosage window as a pure pharmaceutical."},{"time":731000,"text":"We tried it against flu A viruses -- H1N1, H3N2 --"},{"time":735000,"text":"as well as flu B viruses."},{"time":737000,"text":"So then we tried a blend,"},{"time":739000,"text":"and in a blend combination we tried it against H5N1,"},{"time":743000,"text":"and we got greater than 1,000 selectivity index."},{"time":747000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":748000,"text":"I then think that we can make the argument"},{"time":753000,"text":"that we should save the old-growth forest"},{"time":755000,"text":"as a matter of national defense."},{"time":759000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"I became interested in entomopathogenic fungi --"},{"time":766000,"text":"fungi that kill insects."},{"time":768000,"text":"Our house was being destroyed by carpenter ants."},{"time":770000,"text":"So, I went to the EPA homepage, and they were recommending studies"},{"time":773000,"text":"with metarhizium species of a group of fungi"},{"time":776000,"text":"that kill carpenter ants, as well as termites."},{"time":779000,"text":"I did something that nobody else had done."},{"time":781000,"text":"I actually chased the mycelium, when it stopped producing spores."},{"time":784000,"text":"These are spores -- this is in their spores."},{"time":786000,"text":"I was able to morph the culture"},{"time":788000,"text":"into a non-sporulating form."},{"time":790000,"text":"And so the industry has spent over 100 million dollars"},{"time":793000,"text":"specifically on bait stations to prevent termites from eating your house."},{"time":797000,"text":"But the insects aren't stupid,"},{"time":799000,"text":"and they would avoid the spores when they came close,"},{"time":801000,"text":"and so I morphed the cultures into a non-sporulating form."},{"time":804000,"text":"And I got my daughter's Barbie doll dish,"},{"time":806000,"text":"I put it right where a bunch of carpenter ants"},{"time":808000,"text":"were making debris fields, every day,"},{"time":810000,"text":"in my house, and the ants were attracted to the mycelium,"},{"time":814000,"text":"because there's no spores."},{"time":816000,"text":"They gave it to the queen."},{"time":817000,"text":"One week later, I had no sawdust piles whatsoever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820000,"text":"And then -- a delicate dance between dinner and death --"},{"time":826000,"text":"the mycelium is consumed by the ants,"},{"time":829000,"text":"they become mummified, and, boing, a mushroom pops out of their head."},{"time":833000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":834000,"text":"Now after sporulation, the spores repel."},{"time":838000,"text":"So, the house is no longer suitable for invasion."},{"time":842000,"text":"So, you have a near-permanent solution for reinvasion of termites."},{"time":846000,"text":"And so my house came down, I received my first patent"},{"time":849000,"text":"against carpenter ants, termites and fire ants."},{"time":851000,"text":"Then we tried extracts, and lo and behold,"},{"time":854000,"text":"we can steer insects to different directions."},{"time":856000,"text":"This has huge implications."},{"time":858000,"text":"I then received my second patent -- and this is a big one."},{"time":860000,"text":"It's been called an Alexander Graham Bell patent."},{"time":862000,"text":"It covers over 200,000 species."},{"time":864000,"text":"This is the most disruptive technology --"},{"time":866000,"text":"I've been told by executives of the pesticide industry --"},{"time":869000,"text":"that they have ever witnessed."},{"time":871000,"text":"This could totally revamp the pesticide industries throughout the world."},{"time":874000,"text":"You could fly 100 Ph.D. students under the umbrella of this concept,"},{"time":878000,"text":"because my supposition is that entomopathogenic fungi,"},{"time":881000,"text":"prior to sporulation, attract the very insects"},{"time":883000,"text":"that are otherwise repelled by those spores."}]},{"cues":[{"time":886000,"text":"And so I came up with a Life Box, because I needed a delivery system."},{"time":890000,"text":"The Life Box -- you're gonna be getting a DVD of the TED conference --"},{"time":894000,"text":"you add soil, you add water,"},{"time":896000,"text":"you have mycorrhizal and endophytic fungi as well as spores,"},{"time":901000,"text":"like of the Agarikon mushroom."},{"time":903000,"text":"The seeds then are mothered by this mycelium."},{"time":906000,"text":"And then you put tree seeds in here,"},{"time":909000,"text":"and then you end up growing -- potentially --"},{"time":912000,"text":"an old-growth forest from a cardboard box."}]},{"cues":[{"time":914000,"text":"I want to reinvent the delivery system,"},{"time":917000,"text":"and the use of cardboard around the world,"},{"time":919000,"text":"so they become ecological footprints."},{"time":921000,"text":"If there's a YouTube-like site that you could put up,"},{"time":924000,"text":"you could make it interactive, zip code specific --"},{"time":926000,"text":"where people could join together,"},{"time":928000,"text":"and through satellite imaging systems,"},{"time":930000,"text":"through Virtual Earth or Google Earth,"},{"time":932000,"text":"you could confirm carbon credits are being sequestered"},{"time":934000,"text":"by the trees that are coming through Life Boxes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937000,"text":"You could take a cardboard box delivering shoes,"},{"time":940000,"text":"you could add water -- I developed this for the refugee community --"},{"time":944000,"text":"corns, beans and squash and onions."},{"time":946000,"text":"I took several containers -- my wife said, if I could do this, anybody could --"},{"time":950000,"text":"and I ended up growing a seed garden."},{"time":952000,"text":"Then you harvest the seeds --"},{"time":954000,"text":"and thank you, Eric Rasmussen, for your help on this --"},{"time":958000,"text":"and then you're harvesting the seed garden."},{"time":960000,"text":"Then you can harvest the kernels, and then you just need a few kernels."},{"time":964000,"text":"I add mycelium to it, and then I inoculate the corncobs."},{"time":968000,"text":"Now, three corncobs, no other grain --"},{"time":971000,"text":"lots of mushrooms begin to form."},{"time":973000,"text":"Too many withdrawals from the carbon bank,"},{"time":976000,"text":"and so this population will be shut down."},{"time":978000,"text":"But watch what happens here."},{"time":982000,"text":"The mushrooms then are harvested,"},{"time":984000,"text":"but very importantly,"},{"time":988000,"text":"the mycelium has converted the cellulose into fungal sugars."},{"time":991000,"text":"And so I thought, how could we address the energy crisis in this country?"},{"time":998000,"text":"And we came up with Econol."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001000,"text":"Generating ethanol from cellulose using mycelium as an intermediary --"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and you gain all the benefits that I've described to you already."},{"time":1009000,"text":"But to go from cellulose to ethanol is ecologically unintelligent,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and I think that we need to be econologically intelligent"},{"time":1018000,"text":"about the generation of fuels."},{"time":1020000,"text":"So, we build the carbon banks on the planet, renew the soils."},{"time":1023000,"text":"These are a species that we need to join with."},{"time":1026000,"text":"I think engaging mycelium can help save the world."},{"time":1031000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1033000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}